DTEND:20201026T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260624T095702Z
UID:6ppsb2aebo3vn6b25i6co4aqpd@google.com
CREATED:20201018T052108Z
DESCRIPTION:<br>Join us for our second of three pumpkin carving/painting ev
 ents curated by our friends at Shop Local Market.<br>In order to promote ev
 eryone's safety and health\, we will be limiting capacity for these events.
 <br>To reserve your place\, send an email to drink@axelradbeergarden.com wi
 th a guest count for your group (please specify # of children and adults). 
 If in the event that spots fill up\, we can put you on a wait list\, you ca
 n make a reservation for a later time frame via&nbsp\;<a href="https://resy
 .com/cities/hou/axelrad-beer-garden?fbclid=IwAR1WzefFEz-nud5tcohpVEoqRTiQWR
 mH0knM6ywsrBSI4rWM7GLRvXbvkE4">https://resy.com/cities/hou/axelrad-beer-gar
 den</a>\, or we can lock in a spot for you at the upcoming event.<br>*If th
 e time slot that you want isn’t available\, you can select “NOTIFY ME” and 
 it will notify you when there is an opening in your desired time slot. From
  there\, please read all of our new policies to ensure a safe visit for you
  and our staff.<br>*While we will have some supplies\, you are more than we
 lcome to bring your own as well!<br>***Reminder - We are 21+ at 9pm Sundays
  to Thursdays.***
LAST-MODIFIED:20201018T052108Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:PUMPKIN CARVING & PAINTING
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20190915T190000Z
DTEND:20190916T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260624T095702Z
UID:63h9ocvvucor578j4eghmbnpou@google.com
CREATED:20190620T005655Z
DESCRIPTION:"We will be directly funding “Fiel”.  This local grass roots or
 ganization is an immigrant rights organization. They provide pro bono servi
 ces to Houston immigrant residents by aiding in the filing of paperwork and
  in many cases to help stop deportations. They do amazing work in the commu
 nity by holding Information forums and educating students at several local 
 high schools. They are on the frontlines of many civil rights cases and hav
 e provided legal aid to countless low income families. We are proud to be h
 elping with this work."
LAST-MODIFIED:20190629T024031Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Social Justice Bake Sale
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
