BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20230602T000000Z
DTEND:20230602T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260624T095702Z
UID:37h4s2jf6dskf8pir8bt7j70pi@google.com
CREATED:20230412T035058Z
DESCRIPTION:HEX Collective Series at Axelrad\n\nBudget: No budget initially
 . Donations accepted. Potential for artist guarantees after a few shows.\n\
 nLocation: Axelrad Upstairs\n\nDates: Thursdays or Sundays\n\nDoors: 7pm on
  Thursdays\; 3pm on Sundays\n\nStart Time: 7:30pm on Thursdays\; 3:30pm on 
 Sundays\n\nEnd Time: 10:30pm on Thursdays\; 6:30pm on Sundays\n\nRestrictio
 ns: 21+ after 9PM\n\nFirst Show\n\nTitle: Sigil 1 Presented by Hex Collecti
 ve\n\nDate: June 1\, 2023\n\nActs (4): Pretty Dad\; Mishi Bloom\; Annotatio
 n\; Aga Zet+Ryan Hollaway+John Alan Kennedy\n\nSet Times: 7:30pm-7:55pm\; 8
 :15pm-8:40pm\; 9pm-9:25pm\; 9:45pm-10:10pm\n\nSet Order: Pretty Dad\; Mishi
  Bloom\; Annotation\; Aga+Ryan+John\n\nAbout HEX Collective\nHEX (Houston E
 xperimental) Collective's mission is to initiate communities and individual
 s into experimental music\, performance\, and art by making it free and acc
 essible\, welcoming and encouraging participation\, connection\, and collab
 oration between newcomers and existing experimental music and arts communit
 ies\, and organizing a space that practices safety and inclusion\, as well 
 as it does the chaos and deliberation of experimentation. We aim to recogni
 ze\, serve\, and respect existing experimental music and arts communities\,
  and act as an extension of those communities\, while nurturing new spaces 
 for experimentation to evolve. With an understanding that the marginalizati
 on of experimental arts often mirrors the marginalization of its artists\, 
 not only involving but also being shaped\, organized\, and curated by artis
 ts facing marginalization and empowering them through this collective is al
 so paramount to our mission. We do this to pay homage to a community that h
 as supported us beyond measure in terms of artistic growth\, opportunities\
 , and the sharing of music and culture. We wish to inspire the idea that ex
 perimentation is something anyone can do\, all it takes is a desire to and 
 the freeing sense that it is possible.\n\nInstagram: @h.excollective
LAST-MODIFIED:20230413T005109Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hex Collective (Upstairs) Pretty Dad\; Mishi Bloom\; Annotation\; A
 ga Zet+Ryan Hollaway+John Alan Kennedy
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
